## Running the Application

### Start All Services

```bash
sudo ./start.sh
```

**What it does:**
1. Checks prerequisites (Node.js, MongoDB, Python, NGINX, PM2, ML model)
2. Creates required directories (logs, tmp, uploads)
3. Builds frontend if needed
4. Configures NGINX (copies conf, tests, reloads)
5. Starts PM2 cluster (9 instances)
6. Performs health checks on all instances
7. Tests NGINX load balancing
8. Saves PM2 process list

