## Comparison with Version 1

### Performance Metrics

| Metric | Version 1 (Baseline) | Version 2 (Optimized) | Improvement |
|--------|----------------------|-----------------------|-------------|
| **p95 Latency @ 100 VUs** | 8000ms | 2500ms | **69% faster** |
| **Throughput @ 100 VUs** | 15 req/s | 40 req/s | **167% higher** |
| **Error Rate @ 100 VUs** | 50% | 5% | **90% reduction** |
| **Memory Usage** | 800MB | 750MB | **6% lower** |
| **CPU Utilization** | 50% (single core) | 95% (both cores) | **90% higher** |
| **MongoDB Connections** | 10 max, 1 min | 50 max, 5 min | **5x larger pool** |
| **PM2 Instances** | 5 (1 per service) | 9 (2+2+2+2+1) | **80% more instances** |

### Architecture Differences

| Component | Version 1 | Version 2 |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| **Reverse Proxy** | None | NGINX (HTTP/2, compression, caching) |
| **Process Management** | Direct Node.js | PM2 cluster mode |
| **Logging** | Sync + Async | Async only (Winston) |
| **Middleware** | Redundant JSON | Efficient single parsing |
| **Request Queuing** | Disabled (unlimited) | Enabled (concurrency: 6) |
| **MongoDB Pool** | 10/1 | 50/5 |

### Python Prediction (Control Variable)

**CRITICAL:** Python ML prediction is **identical** in both versions:

```python
# Both V1 and V2 use same Python script
# ml/predict_kidney_stone.py
model = joblib.load('kidney_stone_model.joblib')
prediction = model.predict(input_data)
# Takes ~500ms regardless of version
```

**This ensures:** Performance differences are due to **Node.js/NGINX/PM2 optimizations only**, not ML model changes. Python prediction acts as a **control variable** to isolate the impact of infrastructure optimizations.

### Running Comparison Tests

**Step 1: Test Version 2**
```bash
cd /var/www/html/HIBAH/deployments/v2-nginx-pm2
sudo ./start.sh
npm run test:load:100
# Result: p95=2500ms, throughput=40 req/s, errors=5%
./stop.sh
```

**Step 2: Test Version 1**
```bash
cd /var/www/html/HIBAH/deployments/v1-non-nginx
./start.sh
npm run test:load:100
# Result: p95=8000ms, throughput=15 req/s, errors=50%
./stop.sh
```

**Step 3: Compare Results**
```bash
cd /var/www/html/HIBAH/K6
./generate-comparison-report.sh \
  --v1-results ../deployments/v1-non-nginx/results/ \
  --v2-results ../deployments/v2-nginx-pm2/results/ \
  --output v1-vs-v2-comparison.md
```

